            <fr:display-uri>FGOK</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/FGOK/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Translation lookaside buffer">Translation lookaside buffer</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>A small hardware cache of recent virtual-to-physical translations. Without it, every memory reference would incur the cost of walking the <fr:link href="/WALE/" title="Page table" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/WALE/" display-uri="WALE" type="local">Page table</fr:link> in memory.</html:p><html:p>An access proceeds as:</html:p><html:ol><html:li>Extract VPN from the virtual address.</html:li>
  <html:li>Check whether the VPN is in the TLB.</html:li>
  <html:li>TLB hit: read PPN from the entry, append offset, access memory.</html:li>
  <html:li>TLB miss: walk the page table (in hardware on <fr:link href="/L896/" title="CISC vs RISC" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/L896/" display-uri="L896" type="local">CISC</fr:link>, by trapping to OS on <fr:link href="/L896/" title="CISC vs RISC" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/L896/" display-uri="L896" type="local">RISC</fr:link>), insert the translation into the TLB, retry.</html:li></html:ol><html:p>A TLB entry holds the VPN, the PPN, a valid bit (separate from the PTE valid bit — invalid on init, eviction, <fr:link href="/OKCI/" title="Context switch" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/OKCI/" display-uri="OKCI" type="local">context switch</fr:link>), and protection bits.</html:p>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2026</fr:year><fr:month>5</fr:month><fr:day>12</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Problem</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>Each process has different translations for the same VPN, so a naive TLB must be flushed on every <fr:link href="/OKCI/" title="Context switch" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/OKCI/" display-uri="OKCI" type="local">context switch</fr:link>.</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2026</fr:year><fr:month>5</fr:month><fr:day>12</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Solution</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>Add an <html:em>address space identifier</html:em> (ASID) to each TLB entry and an ASID register set on context switch. Now entries from different processes coexist.</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
<fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>7</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:uri>https://kellenkanarios.com/P9UM/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>P9UM</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/P9UM/</fr:route><fr:title text="Culler's Law">Culler's Law</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p><html:em>"Ram is not always ram"</html:em>. Referring to the fact that a physical memory access takes a substantial different amount of time depending on whether it hit in the TLB.</html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2026</fr:year><fr:month>5</fr:month><fr:day>12</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>In real software-managed TLBs, an entry has global bits for shared pages, an 8-bit ASID, coherence bits, and a <html:em>wired</html:em> register reserving slots for code that cannot afford a TLB miss (e.g. the TLB-miss handler itself).</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2026</fr:year><fr:month>5</fr:month><fr:day>12</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>For very fast caches, even a TLB access is a bottleneck. <html:em>Virtually indexed caches</html:em> sidestep the TLB on the index path.</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
</fr:mainmatter>
